answers.answer:
Looks like the problem is with how you are checking whether the video wrapper exists or not: 
if (video_wrapper.length) {
...
}
You should check if video_wrapper is truthy or not, instead of checking the property length:

if (video_wrapper) {
...
}
Also, there is a better approche to do this other than using refs. You can add a state variable to ViewCourse, something like showIframe, and pass it down to ViewOneCourse, then inside ViewOneCourse you would use that variable (showIframe) to render either the image or the iframe.

